                        <p>Letter from Marie Martin to her mother Mary Martin (n√©e Moore). Marie (1892-1975) was later the founder of the Medical Missionaries of Mary. At the outbreak of war in 1914 Marie joined the Voluntary Aid Detachment, a division of the Red Cross. She returned home briefly in 1916 before re-enlisting  two months later and was posted to a field hospital in Heraldo, France.</p>
                    
                        <p></p>
                    
                        <p>Marie is anxious to hear news from home as several members of the family have mumps.</p>
                    
